<br>
I two box a 65 bard/65 mage when i want to grind out for xp's or pharm spectrals. Find any zone where the mobs don't summon, PoV, HoH, wherever, summon a pet, buff pet, turn taunt off, Velocity (a must).  Let bard chant kite until 89% send in pet, at 60% life you can nuke with impunity.  Those percentages are fairly set in stone in my experience.  Send in pet any earlier and quite often he'll gain aggro and eat the rage, nuke any earlier and you're supper.<br>
<br>
In PoV we were killing a mob every 3-3.5 minutes including pull time and rebuff times.  In HoH I'm holding down 6 mob's that are on a 20 min timer.<br>
<br>
What makes bards our PoP ideal partner: 1) Lull, it's godlike not having adds...if you get one your pet is the first to die and you are second unless the bard can gain some sort of aggro 2) Fading Memories, bards don't die and you can gate 3) Requiem of Time, for the rare summonable named that pops and you want his spectral having a 50% slow allows you to effectively chain heal a pet.  When pet dies, bard can chain mez till another pet is ready. 4 ) Bard DoT's do an unbelievable amount of damage and hold aggro almost better than an SK with a HT locked and loaded<br>
<br>
Plus, you are not a leech to a solo bard unless said bard is charm kiting which is almost impossible after you leave PoN/PoD.  Our Rogue pets DPS plus nukes triple his kill speed<br>
<br>
Make a bards day...show him the light)<br>
<br>
Duem the Conjurer<br>
